# Supabase Policy

## Client creation patterns

- Server contexts use `@/lib/supabase/server`.
- Browser contexts use `@/lib/supabase/client`.
- Middleware/session refresh follows `@/lib/supabase/middleware`.
- Privileged operations should use the centralized admin pattern in `@/lib/supabase/admin`.

## Security and authorization

- Enforce ownership checks in server-side actions and queries for coach/client boundaries.
- Treat RLS as primary guardrail and action-level checks as defense in depth.
- Never leak service-role credentials to client components.

## Schema and migrations

- Schema changes must be represented through SQL migrations in `supabase/migrations/`.
- Never rely on dashboard-only schema edits without migration files.
- Regenerate DB types after migration changes; do not hand-edit generated types.

## Query quality

- Prefer explicit selects and typed mapping over broad untyped payloads.
- Keep data reads scoped to minimum required columns.

## Multi-entity consistency

- When one domain action updates multiple related entities, prefer atomic transaction/RPC patterns.
- Avoid partial-update flows that can leave lifecycle state inconsistent across tables.
